    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The article alludes to our national addiction to oil, but it is really our addiction to cars. If we had more compact, walkable villages and cities connected by reliable mass transit, we would need fewer cars and less oil.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The article alludes to our national addiction to oil, but it is really our addiction to cars. If we had more compact, walkable villages and cities connected by reliable mass transit, we would need fewer cars and less oil.</p>
        <p>We can't change America overnight, but we can begin to change those automobile-friendly decisions made every day by government at all levels. Supplemented by a meaningful federal gas tax, that would be the real solution to our dependence on imported energy.  Steve Lanset  Hoboken, N.J.</p>
      </block>
